    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-30T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-30T04:00:00-05:00" n="1027"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1027">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)/3373: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-30T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 30, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>362. My 361, September 28. I understood that at yesterday’s meeting of trade
                    delegations (attended also by Von Papen) Numan steadfastly refused to give any
                    chrome and that Germans while insisting <pb facs="0963" n="955" xml:id="pg_955"
                    /> on their original request and stating that they were awaiting further
                    instructions nevertheless gave the impression of being disposed not to force the
                    issue but to continue the negotiations on the basis of either receiving
                    additional copper or giving less of the highest category materials desired by
                    Turkey.</p>
                <p>Repeated London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
